values: This past weekend was not what I expected it to be.  I went to Austin to go see my sister at UT.  I stayed at a motel.  You would expect it to be a roach motel, but it was actually a cricket hotel because the room that I stayed in was infested with crickets.  I went to Austin on Friday and that night I saw a drunk guy pee on someone's truck.  Being so amused by this, it was then that I realized that I am not quite ready to deal with all the people that act like idiots when they are free to do whatever they want. On Saturday I had to go with my sister to one of her nursing meetings.  It was quite boring with all the lectures and touring of the nursing building.  Then I went back to my personal hell I call my home town.  I was a little bit eager to go home because I was going to meet some college friends of mine, but they ended up leaving me because I got home late.  What did I do after that?  Why, pre-cal and computer science homework of course.  Shows you what kind of life I have on saturday nights.  Sunday I spent the whole day working on more homework.  Fortunately I have monday off, so I can slack off a little bit.  That's about all.

My mom is pissing me off.  I can't stand the whore anymore.  She is always invading my privacy.  I can't wait when I get out of this prison.  I am making my own webpage, but of course my mom is going to  have to see what i put on it.  I feel like a 3 year old.  Damn her.

If you don't want to hear me complain about how much life sucks, then I suggest you hit the "back" button on the toolbar because I'm going to.  I'm going to complain about my dick of a chem teacher.  He is the worst.  This past week I didn't know that we had a homework assignment in class, so I started to do the work in class.  Then Mr. Dick says that he is going to start punishing students like me who don't do their homework and help students that do, such as the whore cheerleader who always seems to be on the good side of teachers because of her breasts and slutty mien.  This cheerleader is always peppy and upbeat and, honestly, it sickens me, so of course she is always the hero of the day.  The problem with this guy is that he is a complete pedophile.  He is always touching girls and squeezing their shoulders and he can get away with it because he is a teacher.  Today there was a pep rally to glorify the people at my school who really don't deserve it.  I, of course, didn't go.  I also am making a "B" in pre-cal which my parents will shoot me for, but I don't really care.  Today in English I found out I made a 98 on an essay over The Scarlet Letter, but my english teacher is a male, so cheerslut will probably get a 100 if she does her act right. Well, c'est la vie.

Well, I've tried updating my journal for the past couple of days, but livejournal hasn't let me.  A couple of days ago I got really angry at my history teacher, Coach Blowhard.  My class was taking a quiz, when this drill team whore talks during one of the bonus questions about how she heard one of the questions on a game show.  I was going to put my opinion in and say "me too", but coach suckass all of a sudden goes "SSHHHHHHHHH".  This doesn't surprise me because this coach will let any girl members of the Friday Night Football bullshit experience get away with anything as long as they promise him oral sex.  He just really is discriminating.  Hmm, not much happened this weekend (I'm trying to act surprised).  I mostly read the scarlet letter, and finished it up and did a mini research project on it.  I think I'm going to write a novel.  I just came up with this conclusion a couple of days ago.  Who knows, I might just get a career out of it.  One thing that really angered me this past weekend was my parents.  Saturday they tried to get me to do with something with them.  I refused so they got fried chicken.  I hate fried chicken, but my parents did get me some cole slaw.  Of course, the cole slaw had to be ruined when I found a pubic hair in it.  Oh yeah, and there is someone besides my parents who are angering me.  It's a friend of mine.  It's a long story, but I have a feeling that she thinks she knows me like the back of her back hand, but she really doesn't.  I really hate it when she says "that's not like you"  to me.  Like she knows whether it's me or not.  She says "people all the time change", yet she never thinks that maybe I'm changing my feelings about the world.  Oh well, that's all.

I hate fried chicken and they didn't tell me they were going to get me chicken, but they did bring home some cole slaw with a pubic hair in it (yummy). After 20 minutes of using the bathroom the door unlocks making it possible for other people to come in.  This prevents prostitutes and drug dealers to have a "private" place on the street. So I haven't written in a long time for good reason.  Now all of my time is dedicated to my precious school, but it's all right because I didn't have much of a social life this summer.  All of my friends are gone.  My last two friends who live in the same city as me have gone to college, leaving me as a junior in high school. High school is a bitch, but I'm not complaining.  It's better than not doing anything at home, but I will definitely not take summer for granted.  I am in a lot of classes with people that I don't exactly like.  Most of them are suck ups and will kiss a lot of teacher's asses.  I like my teachers.  I am in debate and we don't do a thing.  The one class that I can't stand is U.S. History, but I never was a fan of the social studies.  Anways there isn't much else to say.  My mom is going to force me to be in Student Council because I need serious scholarship padding.  Oh well, I'm just hoping that I won't have a nervous breakdown by the end of the school year.

School starts on Monday!  The boring days of summer are finally ending.  Yesterday I went to a concert, but it was a church concert (not exactly the kind of concert I would like to go to). Then today I spent my last day of summer being dragged around a mall by my sister and mother.  That's all that's been happening.

Today I went to a birthday party, and it will be the last one that I go to for a long time.  THe party was at Chuck E. Cheese's a.k.a. the hell hole.  I went there in kindergarten and I thought it was fine, but now I feel that it belongs with other places such as my house on the list of "Places I would rather not be".  There was a the music, the robotic chuck, and children everywhere.  I think the music was the worse.  Every song Chuck sang had the same melody, but different words.  I found it to be one of the most retarded places I  have ever been to.  I didn't play any of the games there.  Someone gave me a token, but I just threw into a crowd just to see what the reaction would be.  That was the most fun I had while there.  If it weren't for the people I went with, I might have just poked my eyeballs out with a fork.  I find it a bit coincidental that Chuck E. Cheese has a name similar to a homicidal doll of Satan.  Then the party went to someone's house, and on the way they played stupid sexually oriented games.  I left at ten because it is a work night for my dad and I have to be home by that time.  Then I read the paper and noticed that this school year my school starts at 8 in the morning.  There is only one week left of summer and I am pretty excited.

Today was the last day of the summer reading program which basically means that today was my last day to volunteer at the library (Hooray!).  Today at the library I talked to this lady, and all she could talk about was her son's wedding that was coming up.  She kept incessantly talking about it and I just kept nodding and saying things such as "yeah", "uh-huh", and "I bet".  All I could think about was all the oxygen she was wasting by talking to me about her son's stupid wedding!  I kept thinking "Is this lady ever going to shut up?"  I maybe got one sentence in.  Then, a friend of the lady came in, those two had so much in common.  For example, they both have the capability to talk until the four horsemen of the apocalypse ride into town.  This new lady could only talk about her new car and how she would kill anybody that touched it.  After she said that, I decided to abstain from talking to her and stay away from her car. The lady also talked about how her child needed braces, and I thought that it would take more than braces to make her daughter look better. I also thought about how these two ladies definitely spend their afternoons at the country club drinking margaritas and spreading all the gossip that they've heard floating around in the god-forsaken town I live in.  I checked out a book today called On the Road by Jack Kerouac, and one of the incessant talkers said "Oh your going to check out a book, good for you!", and I was thinking "What, do I look incapable of reading a book larger than The Cat in the Hat?"  She then said that she has never heard of the book, and I just thought how I'm surprised she knows what a book is.  Today my mom also talked to me about how she was worried that people might think that I am "weird" because of the way that I talk to people in public and the fact that I don't like to talk to people my own age.  That really pissed me off.  I went to sleep because I was really tired after the conversations with that lady.  Tomorrow I will be all by myself at home and it will be great.  I was also invited to a birthday party next thursday.  I know this might sound strange, but I haven't been to a birthday party in 5 years, so I am debating on whether I should ruin my drought or just go.

Yesterday it was the kid's program, so I got to have the pleasure of watching this man imitate farm animals.  I hate kids.  Then, I went and applied at Market Basket.  I thought that they would hire me because they are always hiring students whether they needed them or not.  I filled out an application, and turned it in.  The manager didn't interview me when I turned it in, so I'm thinking that I didn't get the job.  Then I spent the rest of the day sleeping.  Today I woke up and had to work on my 4-H recordbook.  I hate 4-H, but my mom makes me do it anyway.  My mom makes me do a lot of things that I never want to do. In fact she made me go eat dinner with our priest.  This was the highlight of my day.  Nothing like feasting on a bounty of finger foods with your priest.  When i was there, my mom forced me to talk with people my age, which is something that i sometimes have a hard time doing.  Today was one of those days.  When I was there, my dad talked to a guy that said swim team tryouts were all last week.  this pissed my dad off because he wants me to be on the swim team.  i do too, but if i get a job, I won't be able to do both.  So signing up for swim team would be a waste of money.  But my dad, who obviously knows me better than I do myself, said that "I obviously don't want to do swim team, and I'll just quit it just like I do everything else I have ever tried."  Oh well that really pissed me off, and the fact that it was public made it worse.  Oh well, that's about all so I'll let you go.
